Flatlands Avenue, adjoining the N. W. corner of East 40th Street, showing the Norwegian Evangelical Free Church. It was built in 1851 and was known as the First Flatlands Methodist Episcopal Church. In 1925 it was known as St. Peters Protestant Episcopal Church.
